tool_description: Dribbble - Show and tell for designers
name: Dribbble
title: Dribbble

api_list.name: addShotToBucket
api_list.description: Adding a shot to a bucket requires the user to be authenticated with the write scope. The authenticated user must also own the bucket.

required_parameters.name: shotId
required_parameters.description: The ID of the shot to add.

api_list.name: checkOneUserFollowingAnother
api_list.description: Check if one user is following another.

api_list.name: checkYouFollowingUser
api_list.description: Check if you are following a user.

api_list.name: checkYouLikeComment
api_list.description: Checking for a comment like requires the user to be authenticated.

api_list.name: checkYouLikeShot
api_list.description: Checking for a shot like requires the user to be authenticated.

api_list.name: createAttachment
api_list.description: Creating an attachment requires the user to be authenticated with the upload scope. The authenticated user must own the shot and be a pro, a team, or a member of a team.

required_parameters.name: file
required_parameters.description: The attachment file. It must be no larger than 10 megabytes.

api_list.name: createBucket
api_list.description: Creating a bucket requires the user to be authenticated with the write scope.

optional_parameters.name: description
optional_parameters.description: A description of the bucket.

api_list.name: createComment
api_list.description: Creating a comment requires the user to be authenticated with the comment scope. The authenticated user must also be a player or team.

api_list.name: createJob
api_list.description: Create a job.

required_parameters.name: title
required_parameters.description: The title of the job position.

required_parameters.name: url
required_parameters.description: An absolute URL to the full details of the job listing.

required_parameters.name: location
required_parameters.description: The physical location of the position (e.g. “Boston” or “Anywhere”).

required_parameters.name: organizationName
required_parameters.description: The name of the organization the position is with.

optional_parameters.name: team
optional_parameters.description: The integer id or string login of the team that you want associated with the job.

optional_parameters.name: active
optional_parameters.description: true if you want the job to be published immediately.

api_list.name: createShot
api_list.description: Creating a shot requires the user to be authenticated with the upload scope. The authenticated user must also be a player or team.

required_parameters.name: image
required_parameters.description: The image file. It must be exactly 400x300 or 800x600, no larger than eight megabytes, and be a GIF, JPG, or PNG.

optional_parameters.name: description
optional_parameters.description: A description of the shot.

optional_parameters.name: reboundSourceId
optional_parameters.description: An ID of a shot that the new shot is a rebound of. The shot must be reboundable and by a user not blocking the authenticated user.

optional_parameters.name: teamId
optional_parameters.description: An ID of a team to associate the shot with. The authenticated user must either be a member of the team or be authenticated as the same team.

optional_parameters.name: lowProfile
optional_parameters.description: Specify true if the shot is Low Profile.

optional_parameters.name: tags
optional_parameters.description: Tags for the shot.

api_list.name: deleteAttachment
api_list.description: Deleting an attachment requires the user to be authenticated with the upload scope. The authenticated user must also own the attachment.

api_list.name: deleteBucket
api_list.description: Deleting a bucket requires the user to be authenticated with the write scope. The authenticated user must also own the bucket.

api_list.name: deleteComment
api_list.description: Deleting a comment requires the user to be authenticated with the comment scope. The authenticated user must also own the comment.

api_list.name: deleteShot
api_list.description: Deleting a shot requires the user to be authenticated with the upload scope. The authenticated user must also own the shot.

api_list.name: followUser
api_list.description: Following a user requires the user to be authenticated with the write scope.

api_list.name: getAccessToken
api_list.description: Returns access token.

required_parameters.name: clientSecret
required_parameters.description: The client secret you received from Dribbble when you registered.

required_parameters.name: redirectUri
required_parameters.description: The URL in your application where users will be sent after authorization.

required_parameters.name: code
required_parameters.description: The OAuth verification code acquired via OAuth's web authentication protocol.

required_parameters.name: clientId
required_parameters.description: The client ID you received from Dribbble when you registered.

api_list.name: getShots
api_list.description: List shots.

optional_parameters.name: sort
optional_parameters.description: The sort field with the following possible values: comments, recent, views

optional_parameters.name: timeframe
optional_parameters.description: A period of time to limit the results to with the following possible values: week, month, year, ever

optional_parameters.name: list
optional_parameters.description: Limit the results to a specific type with the following possible values: animated, attachments, debuts, playoffs, rebounds, teams

optional_parameters.name: date
optional_parameters.description: Limit the timeframe to a specific date, week, month, or year.

api_list.name: getShotsForUsersFollowedByUser
api_list.description: Listing shots from followed users requires the user to be authenticated with the public scope. Also note that you can not retrieve more than 600 results, regardless of the number requested per page.
